x\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mu_{0}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">μ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>","key":"jLdGHzzgdg"},{"type":"text","value":" falls outside the confidence interval, reject H~o~.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"oaQijOcwtG"}],"key":"PqtS5t2bVH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If ","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"pZc1XVQ4n6"},{"type":"inlineMath","value":"\\mu_{0}","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"html":"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mu_{0}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">μ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>","key":"Jga8wbhclR"},{"type":"text","value":" falls inside the confidence interval, do not reject H~o~.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"YGviaMXdnt"}],"key":"llKD9bnL8Q"},{"type":"admonition","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"usJK973QFf"}],"key":"k68iGgLn27"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"We'll use example 2, in which the alternative was two-sided.\n\nRecall that we want to check whether a medication conforms to a target concentration of a chemical ingredient by testing\n\n$H_{0}:\\mu=250$\n\n$H_{a}:\\mu\\neq250$\n\nWe assume that $\\sigma=12$, and in a sample of size n = 100 we obtained a sample mean of $\\bar{x}=247$.\n\nA 95% confidence interval for μ is $\\bar{x}\\pm2\\frac{\\sigma}{\\sqrt{n}}=247\\pm2\\frac{12}{\\sqrt{100}}=247\\pm2.4=\\left(244.6, 249.4\\right)$.\n\nSince the interval does not contain 250, we reject H~o~ and conclude that the alternative is true: the population mean concentration differs from 250.\n\n```{figure} images/image354.gif\n:alt: A number line showing the 95% confidence interval, which is (244.6, 249.4). 250 is also marked on the number line, and it isn&apos;t within the interval, so we can be confident that μ isn&apos;t 250. In other words, we can reject the hypothesis H_0:μ = 250\n\nA number line showing the 95% confidence interval, which is (244.6, 249.4). 250 is also marked on the number line, and it isn&apos;t within the interval, so we can be confident that μ isn&apos;t 250. In other words, we can reject the hypothesis H_0:μ = 250\n```","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"EGMHM8aUwU"}],"key":"qWE5UC4NHH"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Did I Get This?","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"key":"iEM34jflSe"}],"identifier":"did-i-get-this","label":"Did I Get This?","html_id":"did-i-get-this","implicit":true,"key":"xD0uLZGkbJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":41,"column":1},"end":{"line":41,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One of the following is an actual Minitab output; the others were edited to be incorrect.","position":{"start":{"line":41,"column":1},"end":{"line":41,"column":1}},"key":"gstYJU1Dhz"}],"key":"fKsn9DplF7"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/build/image392-1db9ecc37804467b7a586d9bb9a76511.gif","alt":"Output: One-Sample Z: Test of mu=264 vs not = 264 The assumed standard deviation = 16 N: 35 Mean: 260.000 SE Mean: 2.704 95% CI: (254.699, 265.301) Z: -2.22 P: 0.047","key":"Cdb1hICsfz","urlSource":"images/image392.gif"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Output: One-Sample Z: Test of mu=264 vs not = 264 The assumed standard deviation = 16 N: 35 Mean: 260.000 SE Mean: 2.704 95% CI: (254.699, 265.301) Z: -2.22 P: 0.047","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"FVxbtjUaLA"}],"key":"AnsoNvGRnC"}],"key":"rEwwTXmPJT"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"ioL4xKhUW9"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type