μ would be. In particular, we can conclude that since the confidence interval lies below 250, at least a large portion of the shipment contains medication that is ineffective.","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"IaJd065ZGR"}],"key":"l3SPo6DP0F"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"ZPITpbHMjP"}],"key":"woVuVgmrog"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Learn By Doing**\n\nHypothesis Testing for the Population Mean\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":82,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"key":"GZngJ7httR"}],"key":"CyKOR8p8yE"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Do you feel that you understand this concept?","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"IajSQIeaMb"}],"key":"gWbGnefX9o"},{"type":"text","value":" If so, then go ahead and move on. If not, then click the link below for some additional practice.","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"mUtK0L1d8s"}],"key":"bgoHSdW7qC"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"EdjoOsfZHd"}],"key":"ruREl2Xn8h"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Learn By Doing**\n\nHypothesis Testing for the Population Mean (Extra Problems)\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"key":"u82iXo884N"}],"key":"xjV1kpjjDe"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We are done with the case where the population standard deviation, σ, i